cute indeed.  two problems, though:

-&gt;  for a very long while (and perhaps currently also) it took
too much time to get info in the LIST-OF-LISTS updated (apparently
Zellich has other work to do, too :-&gt;)  if the information takes long
enough to get into the LIST-OF-LISTS, the information in the mail.list
domain should probably be out-of-date for some time.  

-&gt;  this takes some flexibility and control of the list out of the
hands of the list maintainers.  it no longer is enough to keep the
list membership up to date; list maintainers have to be sure to inform
the MX record keeper (or the list-of-lists keeper) of the right things
to change.  my experience is that folks aren't very good about this.

if i (as a list owner) can get the list information changed in a (business)
day or two, then this would be cool.


